Argentina Will Increase Minimum Wage by 25%, Ambito Reports

-- B y   E l i a n a   R a s z e w s k i
-- 
2011-08-02T12:26:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-02/argentina-will-increase-minimum-wage-by-25-ambito-reports.html
Argentina ’s government will raise the
country’s minimum wage by 25 percent to about 2,300 pesos ($558)
a month, newspaper Ambito Financiero said, without explaining
how it obtained the information.  President  Cristina Fernandez de Kirchner  will make the
announcement before the primary elections that will be held on
Aug. 14, the Buenos Aires-based newspaper said.  The increase will benefit 700,000 workers, Ambito said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eliana Raszewski in Buenos Aires at 
 eraszewski@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Goodman at 
 jgoodman19@bloomberg.net  